PULMONARY
DISEASES
IN
CHILDHOOD
MANY
TYPES
OF
LUNG
DISEASE
ARE
SEEN
IN
THE
PEDIATRIC
AGE
GROUP
THESE
RANGE
ALL
THE
WAY
FROM
DISORDERS
OF
THE
NEONATE
THAT
ARE
CLOSELY
RELATED
TO
PARTURITION
TO
ACUTE
INFECTIOUS
DISEASES
SEEN
IN
INFANCY
AND
EARLY
CHILDHOOD
TO
CHRONIC
DISORDERS
SUCH
AS
CYSTIC
FIBROSIS
AND
BRONCHIAL
ASTHMA
MANAGEMENT
OF
THE
CONDITIONS
DESCRIBED
INVOLVES
COOPERATION
BETWEEN
THE
PRIMARY
CARE
PHYSICIAN
AND
THE
SPECIALIST
A
VARIETY
OF
ORGANIZATIONS
OFFERS
AID
TO
BOTH
PHYSICIANS
AND
PATIENTS
FAMILIES
